{"id":"project-LICHEN-xujr","title":"SCHC: OSCORE rules 5/6 use wrong address compression format","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/schc/schc.c
Lines: 781-794 (compress) and 959-976 (decompress)

Rule 5 (SCHC_RULE_LINK_LOCAL_OSCORE) is designed for link-local OSCORE traffic
but uses the wrong address compression format.

In compress_coap(), the address format is selected by:
```c
if (rule_id == SCHC_RULE_LINK_LOCAL_COAP) {
    // Send only IID (64 bits)
} else {
    // Send full 128-bit addresses
}
```

SCHC_RULE_LINK_LOCAL_COAP is 0, but rule 5 is SCHC_RULE_LINK_LOCAL_OSCORE.
Rule 5 validates addresses as link-local but compresses them as global (full 128 bits).

Impact: Rule 5 wastes 8 bytes per packet (128 bits each for src/dst instead of 64 bits).
The compression/decompression are consistent so no data corruption occurs.

Fix: Update conditions to include OSCORE variants:
```c
if (rule_id == SCHC_RULE_LINK_LOCAL_COAP || 
    rule_id == SCHC_RULE_LINK_LOCAL_OSCORE) {
    // Send only IID (64 bits)
} else {
    // Send full 128-bit addresses
}
```

Same fix needed in decompress_coap() at line 959 and for min_residue calculation at line 944.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T17:30:29.711138Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T17:30:29.711169Z"}

